assignee: codex-agent
author: codex-agent
estimated_minutes: 300
acceptance_criteria: "A governance normalize command can (1) scan and report placeholder/low-signal metadata patterns, (2) emit deterministic mutation previews, and (3) apply approved updates while preserving history and ownership semantics."
definition_of_ready: Pattern catalog and replacement policies are captured from completed governance sweeps.
goal: Governance operations by default
objective: Replace manual metadata normalization scripts
value: Reduces manual command volume and inconsistent cleanup outcomes
impact: Improves repeatability and lowers operational error risk
outcome: Agents can run governance normalization from a supported pm command
why_now: Recent sweep required >400 scripted metadata mutations that should be productized.
